{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"condemned-adobe-zebrafish","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Why\n\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py` is a grandfathered over-cap module (currently 971 LOC; soft cap 800). It carries a row in `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt`, `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt` (975), and a remedy row in docs/architecture.md. This story graduates it off the module-size gate by extracting a cohesive leaf of pure helpers.\n\n## What\n\nCreate a new pure leaf module `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_lint.py` (DetResult-free, re-only deterministic text/graph helpers), mirroring the existing sibling `det_operator_attested.py`. MOVE three cohesive islands out of det_floor:\n\n1. Verify-command lint (G-3a / WS4): `_VERIFY_*`, `_GREP_*`, `_SHELL_VAR_RE`, `_lint_verify_command`, `_verify_command_strings`.\n2. G5 decomposition-veto cluster: `decomposition_state_block`, `_G5_UNDECOMPOSED_RE`, `_is_undecomposed_claim`, `veto_undecomposed_g5`.\n3. Pure task-DAG graph helpers: `_find_cycle`, `_file_interference`.\n\nThe `DET_CHECKS` registry and all p1-p9 check functions STAY in det_floor. `p5_task_dag` real-imports `_find_cycle`/`_file_interference`; `p6_ac_quality` real-imports `_lint_verify_command`/`_verify_command_strings`; det_floor re-exports `decomposition_state_block`/`veto_undecomposed_g5` (# noqa: F401) for pass1.py + test_g5_decomp_det.py. The leaf references `PlanContext` only as a type annotation, imported under `if TYPE_CHECKING` with `from __future__ import annotations` first, so it is a true runtime leaf (no runtime import of det_floor).\n\n## DEVIATION from docs/architecture.md remedy row\n\nThe arch.md offenders row proposes extracting ONLY the verify-command-lint cluster into `det_verify_lint.py`. That row is superseded: the verify-lint cluster alone is SUB-FLOOR (<100 LOC) AND would leave det_floor still over the 800 cap. This ticket therefore WIDENS the seam — it moves the verify-lint island, the G5 decomposition-veto island, and the pure graph helpers (`_find_cycle`/`_file_interference`) into one `det_lint.py` leaf. The stale arch.md row is deleted by this ticket. This is a pure, mechanical refactor (no signature/logic change; symbols relocated + re-exported); E5 testing-plan is not-applicable — the existing tests are the oracle.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] New leaf `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_lint.py` exists and is in [100, 800] LOC (verify: wc -l)\n- [ ] `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/det_floor.py` is <= 800 LOC (verify: wc -l)\n- [ ] det_floor.py removed from .github/module-size-allowlist.txt AND .github/module-size-ceilings.txt; its docs/architecture.md offenders-table row deleted (verify: grep -c det_floor on all three)\n- [ ] tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py passes (verify: python -m pytest that file -q)\n- [ ] Back-compat: det_floor still exposes decomposition_state_block and veto_undecomposed_g5 (re-exported); pass1.py and test_g5_decomp_det.py unchanged\n- [ ] Named suites green: python -m pytest tests/unit/test_plan_review.py tests/unit/test_g5_decomp_det.py tests/unit/test_det_floor_operator_attested.py tests/unit/test_det_invariants.py -q","id":"e73b-71d5-e6d5-4d28","parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","priority":1,"tags":["module-size"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Split det_floor.py: extract pure text/graph helpers into det_lint.py leaf"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784397466611342001,"uuid":"85718173-2c1c-452f-869c-da9c8cb9b733"}